Text.SourceString: It’s good to see you out and about.//Have you introduced yourself to the townies?
We’ve been setting aside recyclables in that lot near the park.//I’m hoping someday we can build something there.
I think the islanders here already have the right mindset to reduce, reuse, and recycle.//It’s a shame we don’t have an appropriate facility for it.
We’ve been setting aside recyclables in that lot near the park.//I’m hoping someday we can build something there.
I think the islanders here already have the right mindset to reduce, reuse, and recycle.//It’s a shame we don’t have an appropriate facility for it.
Can you imagine how much trash there actually is at sea?
I hope we can clean up the trash on the ocean floor someday, so we can finally start our coral reef nursery.
Can you imagine how much trash there actually is at sea?
I hope we can clean up the trash on the ocean floor someday, so we can finally start our coral reef nursery.
We’ve been setting aside recyclables in that lot near the park.//I’m hoping someday we can build something there.
I think the islanders here already have the right mindset to reduce, reuse, and recycle.//It’s a shame we don’t have an appropriate facility for it.
Our goal is to build a recycling center for the locals to use.//Hopefully, we can teach our youth and they can carry the tradition forward.
Our goal is to build a recycling center for the locals to use.//Hopefully, we can teach our youth and they can carry the tradition forward.
Can you imagine how much trash there actually is at sea?
I hope we can clean up the trash on the ocean floor someday, so we can finally start our coral reef nursery.
Looking for some work to do, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=happy>Ah, I was just thinking, wouldn’t it be nice if we could have a community garden?
It would be nice to have a place where the community can grow crops, bond, and share our produce.
There’s a list of community upgrades that we can do.//It’s in the community center.
There aren’t that many items on the list for now, but I think we should add to it once we see how our island progresses.
For the community upgrade, I think it’s important to start where we’ll have the most impact.//This means building a community garden.
We should put the resources into significantly improving our island and our standard of living.
For the community upgrade, I think it’s important to start where we’ll have the most impact.//This means building a community garden.
We should put the resources into significantly improving our island and our standard of living.
How was your weekend?//<portrait=happy>I’m going to start this week off with a cup of the tavern’s coffee.
I got some over the weekend and left it to chill in the fridge.//I keep the empty cups and use them as planters.
It must take plenty of work to get your farm ready for planting every season.
I’m no farmer, but clearing weeds is probably the first step.//Would you agree?
I don’t think you need a fancy tool for it.//I believe that your standard scythe will do.
If you want to upgrade any of your tools, bring them over to the <NpcName>Sanchezes</>’ shop.//They know what they’re doing.
They live in the woodlands, just across the river from my house.
Did you really see a mermaid?//<portrait=happy>Ah! You got me again. Nice one, <PlayerName>$player</>!
I admit, shopping can get addictive.
I should probably update the bulletin board today and make sure there aren’t any outdated posts.
If you want to keep track of people’s birthdays, there’s a calendar near the community center.//Don’t worry, I make sure to update it every season.
Birthday presents are the quickest way to make friends.//<portrait=happy>I particularly like sake, but I wouldn’t turn down some pineapple upside-down cake either.
Can you believe it’s almost the weekend already?
The week goes by really fast when you’re having fun or have a lot to do.//<portrait=happy>Yours must fly by!
Do you have any plans for the weekend?
Ah, I see…//I’ll probably go to the tavern tonight and catch up with folks.
<NpcName>Frank</> makes a mean pasta.//The kids love it.
Birthday presents are the quickest way to make friends.
I particularly like sake, but I wouldn’t turn down some pineapple upside-down cake either.
Have you watched the new commercial on TV yet?//From what I’ve seen, <NpcName>Luke</> has an eye for quality electronics.
Preparing for the new week, <PlayerName>$player</>?
The weather is perfect for diving.
I need to visit Socket Electronics today and ask <NpcName>Luke</> where my new blender is.
Ah, darn… Socket is closed today.
I’m going to treat myself to a pineapple upside-down cake today.
<NpcName>Sam</> carries a different variety of crops every year.//I hope he brings back durian next year.
Durian sure is my guilty pleasure.
I AM rather busy.//I have many things on the agenda this season, but I still like to take a fishing break here and there.
You should talk to <NpcName>Sunny</> at Beach Shack if you have any questions about fishing.
Yes, he’s <NpcName>Oliver</>’s dad and is the one near the cash register.//<portrait=happy>Not the one in the kitchen.
Some of the islanders like to do group yoga at the community center every Saturday morning.
Of course you can join.//<portrait=normal><NPCName>Leah</> usually leads the class.
Happy Thursday, <PlayerName>$player</>!
Coral Island has very fertile soil.//You can grow almost anything here.
And the fishing, of course.//You can catch salmon at sea all Summer long.
We are incredibly blessed here, with the weather and fertile soil, and not too many rat problems.//To give back, it’s important for us to take care of our environment.
The rat problem could have been way worse.//<portrait=annoyed>I heard from my other mayor friend that it destroyed their community center.//<portrait=normal>Thankfully, it’s all restored by now.
Back in the day, I would spend my Saturdays at the beach from sunrise to sundown.
Ah, the good old days…
Have you tried growing grass?//You can cut it and it will automatically be deposited into your silo as animal feed.
Sometimes <NpcName>Ben</> has seeds that <NpcName>Sam</> doesn’t carry.//If you want to check it out, <NpcName>Ben</> opens late today.
I’m not exactly sure about <NpcName>Ben</>’s store hours.//<portrait=normal>I don’t go to that part of the forest very often.
<NpcName>Ben</>'s usually out of town the last two weeks of Fall.//He likes to go on adventures, that one.
Hmm… That is true. His eyes do always look red.//He must not sleep very much.//<portrait=normal>That young man must have plenty of work to do.
I might go and say hi to him next week…
I think the last time I went to your farm was when you first moved to the island.//<portrait=happy>Do you remember that?
It feels like ages ago.//You’ve become a part of the community now.
Part of my job is to check in on local businesses and make sure they’re doing okay.//I also make sure they’re on time with their taxes.
I’ve spoken to the governor about lowering our taxes here, and increasing the school budget.
It isn’t in my power to change the law, but there’s nothing wrong with trying.
Should we put in another request for a community garden?//I can see it being beneficial to the islanders.
But I’m not sure how I can get the funding for that.//It’s a bit tight with us trying to keep our festivals running every year.//The governor may not like the idea very much.
I used to run a general store in the downtown area, back in my youth. But then Mayor <NpcName>Leanne</> passed away.
At a town meeting, I decided to ask if I should try running to replace her. There seemed to be support for me, so I did.
I saw this town panic about a flu outbreak some years ago. People were worried about stocking up food, which depleted our food supply very fast.
Thankfully, we got this contained quickly and the hysteria settled. But it was one expensive year for the town.
I’m proud to say that we have excellent doctors living here.
I’m sure it’s just a matter of time before Coral Island attracts more talented people, like you.
I’ve spent my life taking care of Coral Island. I never got to take <NpcName>Carol</> to see the world and now I spend sleepless nights regretting it.
At the moment, I don’t feel like traveling anymore. Because if it’s just me, is it even worth it?
Another week is right around the corner. Are you planting anything new at the farm?
I always have less work on the weekend, except for when we hold festivals.
I saw this town panic about a flu outbreak some years ago. People were worried about stocking up food, which depleted our food supply very fast.
Thankfully, we got this contained quickly and the hysteria settled. But it was one expensive year for the town.
It’s nice to see the youth getting more and more involved in the community.
You are setting an excellent example for all of us, <PlayerName>$player</>. Keep up the good work!
How was your first week on the farm?//It’s been a while since someone stayed at that cabin.
I’m not too happy about announcing Pufferfish’s arrival next week.//But the islanders need to know as soon as possible.

The space they’ll occupy is theirs, to begin with.//<portrait=normal>The governor let me know they were planning to purchase your farm, but it seems like you beat them to it. So they moved here looking to buy another spot.

Pufferfish is looking to start drilling on our island.//The only thing that was stopping them from moving their cranes here was their lack of property.//They’re interested in buying us out, then drilling as much oil as possible to expand their business.
Pufferfish is building a mini golf course for the community and trying to buy us out.//<portrait=concerned>So, I think as long as we don’t sell our property, we have nothing to worry about.
Have you planted any Spring seeds yet?//<portrait=happy>Sugarcane is my personal favorite.
It does take a while to grow, but we do grow the sweetest sugarcane around here.//<portrait=happy>I’m sure <NpcName>Sam</> would pay a lot for it.
Spring is my least favorite season because, you know…taxes.
Well, that was harsh of me.//<portrait=happy>Spring is great, actually, with all the colorful tulips growing around the island. Bamboo shoots!
Are you ready for Summer?//<portrait=happy>The beach is very vibrant this time of year!
You should keep some of your Spring vegetables in a chest, in case you need them for something.
Letting too many tax documents pile up can be mentally draining at times.//<portrait=normal>It’s good to get them done early.
Remember that we have a Cherry Blossom Potluck tomorrow. There will be so much food!//See you there!
What is a better way to celebrate Spring, eh?
Summer is here! Ah, I can feel the sun on my skin! Life’s good, eh?
Are you going to plant pineapples this Summer? <NpcName>Sam</> might have seeds this year.
I’m glad <NpcName>Nina</> is coming to visit. I remember when she was born. The celebration was out of this world.
I usually spend my Summer weekends at Beach Shack, catching up with <NpcName>Nina</>.
I think I’m going to visit the <NpcName>Sanchezes</> tomorrow and see what they’ve been up to.
They’re a lot of fun to chat with. That <NpcName>Pablo</> always has some stories!
There’s no better time for me to tighten my hat. Now that the sun is blazing nonstop, I need this hat on me at all times.
Summer is here!
Are you having a productive Summer, <PlayerName>$player</>? Because I sure am.
Plenty of people want to join our Mooncake Festival. But with the limited town budget, I have to make sure that our merchants get their booths first, before adding more.
I hate to police merchants’ booths at festivals, but there are regulations that people need to follow. We can’t just approve every design. What if it looks out of place?
I wish, someday, someone would create a warm fizzy drink with dried pumpkin in it.
I would call it “pumpkin extract drink.” Sounds good, doesn’t it?
You guys have a pumpkin extract drink in Pokyo?! Lucky you.
You probably can’t farm all that much in this harsh weather, eh <PlayerName>$player</>?
It may be a good time to check out some other areas on this island. Or, perhaps, make friends.
How’s the farm doing? I hope the old house is holding up okay.
I haven’t seen rain this hard since…hmm…//<portrait=happy>Since the last time it rained, I guess.//Apologies, rainy days make my head a bit fuzzy.
I can’t hear you! Let’s get indoors and continue to chat.
There is something about rainy nights. So soothing.
No matter the season, it gets fairly cold when it rains here.
*hurrying somewhere*
Oh, my! It’s been a while since it stormed like this!
*hurrying somewhere*
How are your plants holding up during the storm?
*hurrying somewhere*
Doesn’t this town, covered in snow like this, remind you of that town from that movie?!
Umm… I can’t think of the name, but you know what I’m talking about.//<portrait=happy>The famous movie! With the snow and the town.
Anyway, how’s your day been?
Doesn’t this town, covered in snow like this, remind you of that town from that movie?!
Umm… I can’t think of the name, but you know what I’m talking about.//<portrait=happy>The famous movie! With the snow and the town.
Anyway, how’s your day been?
Doesn’t this town, covered in snow like this, remind you of that town from that movie?!
Good day, <PlayerName>$player</>! I’m happy to see the locals are supporting each other.
I just had a friendly chat next door and I thought I’d come here to check out what <NpcName>Luke</> has in stock.
How’s the farm doing?//I hope the old house is holding up okay.
I’ve been sporting this hairstyle since I was eighteen.//Perhaps it’s time for a change.
Nah! People seem to like it.//I’m keeping this style.
One of these days, I’m going to show you my old general store.
It’s right next door.//<NpcName>Luke</> runs an electronics store there now.
Hi, there, <PlayerName>$player</>.//Enjoying yourself?

I’ve heard people say you shouldn’t mix business with pleasure.//Well, I don’t know what to tell ya, but I’m here to check up on local businesses.//<portrait=happy>It doesn’t stop me from enjoying myself, does it?
I don’t think so.//<portrait=normal>To make a point, I’m about to show you how much fun I’m having.//Just hang on a minute, you don’t want to miss my classic dance moves.
I used to be quite the fun machine back in the day.
What’s a Sunday without a little trip to the tavern, right <PlayerName>$player</>?
I’m debating whether I should take some cake home.//You know, for tomorrow.
Don’t let me stop you from mingling!
Heh heh... I’ve heard that story at least three times now, and it seems like it gets funnier and funnier each time.
The beach is stunning this time of year.
The sea right here, <PlayerName>$player</>, is home to many creatures.
Fancy a room for a getaway weekend?
Just collecting data from <NpcName>Suki</> to monitor our tourism industry.//I’m also restocking our town’s brochures for the guests.

<NpcName>Luke</> helped me make the brochures.//Hmm… I can see that we could certainly use a new design.//<portrait=happy>This one is kind of outdated. Do you know anything about design, by any chance?
Do you know <NpcName>Joko</> and <NpcName>Dinda</> well?
Have you tried their pineapple upside-down cakes?
<NpcName>Sam</> doesn’t give a discount.//<portrait=normal>I’ve known him for years and years, and I have never been given any sort of markdown.//Or even a rebate, for crying out loud.
Well, okay. <NpcName>Sam</> carries the best-quality produce, and to be fair, his price isn’t too bad.//<portrait=happy>So, you’re right. I really can’t complain, can I?
Got all you need?
Unbelievable view from up here.
